{
  "url": "https://www.w3schools.com/js/js_object_method.asp",
  "title": "JavaScript",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "JavaScript Object Methods"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "Object methods are actions that can be performed on objects.\nA method is a function definition stored as a property value."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Property",
          "Value"
        ],
        [
          "firstName",
          "John"
        ],
        [
          "lastName",
          "Doe"
        ],
        [
          "age",
          "50"
        ],
        [
          "eyeColor",
          "blue"
        ],
        [
          "fullName",
          "function() {return this.firstName + \" \" + this.lastName;}"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "const person = {\n    firstName: \"John\",\n  lastName: \"Doe\",\n  id: 5566,\n  fullName: function() {\n    return this.firstName + \" \" + \nthis.lastName;  }\n};"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In the example above, this refers to the person object:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "this.firstName means the firstName property of person."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "this.lastName means the lastName property of person."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Accessing Object Methods"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You access an object method with the following syntax:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "unknown",
      "code": "objectName.methodName()"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you invoke the fullName property with (), it will execute as a function:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "name = person.fullName();"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you access the fullName property without (), it \nwill return the function definition:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "name = person.fullName;"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Adding a Method to an Object"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Adding a new method to an object is easy:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "person.name = function () {  return this.firstName + \" \" + this.lastName;};"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Using JavaScript Methods"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This example uses the JavaScript toUpperCase() method to convert a text \nto uppercase:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "person.name = function () {\n  return (this.firstName + \" \" + this.lastName).toUpperCase();\n};"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "Learn More:\nJavaScript Object Definitions\nJavaScript Object Constructors\nJavaScript Object this\nJavaScript Object Methods\nJavaScript Object Properties\nJavaScript Object Getters & Setters\nJavaScript Object Protection\nJavaScript Object Reference"
    }
  ]
}